  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Remove the lemongrass husk and peel the ginger and garlic, then put all the marinade ingredients into a blender or pestle and mortar and blitz or grind until smooth – it will be quite loose. Pour everything into a large bowl, add the chicken and marinate for at least 20 mins (or up to two days) in the fridge."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Heat the oven to 180°C. Slice the white onion and put into the bottom of a dutch oven or casserole dish. Add the chicken (skin-side up) and marinade on top of the onions, add a lid and cook in the oven for 25 mins."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "After 25 mins, remove the lid and turn the heat up to 220°C. Put the dish on the top shelf of the oven and cook for 10-15 mins, to sear the chicken skin. Remove from the oven and set aside to rest for at least 10 mins."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Meanwhile, make the nước chấm dressing. Mince the garlic and ginger, finely chop the chilli, then combine all the ingredients in a small bowl. Mix well to dissolve the sugar and set aside."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "For the noodle salad, place the vermicelli noodles into a medium-sized bowl and cover with boiling water. Leave for 4-5 mins. The noodles should be cooked through but still hold their shape, so taste at 4 mins in. Strain as soon as there is no more raw bite and set aside in the same bowl."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Meanwhile, slice the carrot and cucumber into thin matchsticks, or use a peeler to make ribbons, then set aside on a large plate. Finely slice the lettuce, mint and coriander, then set aside on the same plate."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "When the chicken has slightly cooled, remove the bones and cut into slices."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Divide the noodles between four serving bowls, then top with the vegetables, herbs and sliced chicken pieces. Drizzle all over with a few tbsp dressing and some spoons of the chicken gravy. Garnish with peanuts, crispy shallots and a lime wedge."
    }
  ],
